	<title>Exercises: On the Extended Real Number Line</title>
	<exercise>
		<problem>
			<para>According to the conventions of computing with infinities, decide whether the following operations are defined; if yes, what is the answer?</para>
		</problem>
		<part>
			<problem>
				<para><latex>3 + \infty</latex></para>
			</problem>
			<approach>
				<answer><para><latex>3+\infty = \infty</latex></para></answer>
			</approach>
		</part>
		<part>
			<problem>
				<para><latex>(4-\infty)\cdot (-\infty)</latex></para>
			</problem>
			<approach>
				<answer><para><latex>(4-\infty)\cdot (-\infty) = (-\infty)\cdot (-\infty) = +\infty</latex></para></answer>
			</approach>
		</part>
		<part>
			<problem>
				<para><latex>(10 - \infty) + ( -(10^{100}) + \infty)</latex></para>
			</problem>
			<approach>
				<answer><para>This operation is not defined</para></answer>
				<solution.hint><para>The operation in each bracket is defined. What is the answer for each bracket?</para></solution.hint>
				<solution>
					<para>We have the computations</para>
					<computation>
						<left>10 - \infty</left>
						<center>=</center>
						<right>-\infty</right>
						<left>-(10^{100}) + \infty</left>
						<center>=</center>
						<right>+\infty</right>
					</computation>
					<para>According to the conventions of computing with infinities, <latex>(-\infty) + \infty</latex> is not defined.</para>
				</solution>
			</approach>
		</part>
		<part>
			<problem><para><latex>\SqBr{(-(10^{100} + \infty) + (37 + \infty)}\cdot (\infty)</latex></para></problem>
			<approach>
				<answer><para><latex>\SqBr{(-(10^{100} + \infty) + (37 + \infty)}\cdot (+\infty) = \SqBr{ (+\infty) + (+\infty) } \cdot (+\infty) = +\infty</latex></para></answer>
			</approach>
		</part>
	</exercise>
</exercise.pack>